This paper deals with secure communications in a relay channel using lattice codes, which falls under the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. It also involves the concept of weak secrecy, which is a topic in cryptography and security (cs.CR). The use of a relay and the half-duplex operation suggests that it may also be relevant to the networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. The paper also discusses the single-input single-output (SISO) and multiple-input single-output (MISO) channels, which are topics in signal processing and machine learning (cs.SI, cs.MM).
